      <h3>1-Dmitry Klokov</h3>
            <p>Klokov was born in Balashikha, the son of Vyacheslav Klokov, who was a world champion in the Heavyweight category. Married to Elena, and have a daughter named Anastasia</p>
        <p>Klokov became world champion at the 2005 World Championships.
        Klokov won the silver medal at the 2008 Summer Olympics. He won the silver medal at the 2011 World Weightlifting Championships. He lost to a fellow Russian, Khadzhimurat Akkayev by 2 kilos (on the snatch). Klokov was scheduled to compete at the 2012 Summer Olympics in the 105 kg class but was forced to withdraw due to undisclosed medical reasons.
<p><b>In May 2015, Klokov announced his retirement from international competition.</b></p>

 <h3>2-Youtube Channel</h3>
            <p>Launched in 2010, with almost 200K subscribers and over 40million total views. Dmitry, publishes videos of his seminars, training and events that he attends. It is like of a vlog
            sometimes he interview champions of record the training camp that he have established.
            <br><b> It is very inspiring for athletes to watch or weightlifters/people who seek to get stronger and fitter!</b></p>
<br>
 <h3>3-What makes him so unique?</h3>

   <img class="img-fluid rounded" src="{{ asset('main/img/dmitry-klokov.png') }}" alt="">
           <br> <p>Before getting into the business world. Dmitry was well know to be a phenomenal athlete who started weightlifting at 11 years old.</p>
             <p>He worked hard and sucrified since his childhood to be the person he is, today. However, what fascinated me the most, a part from 20 years of a successful career, He kept lifting as he
              was preparing for the olympic. Doing some fantastic results, that actual competitors are struggling to do.</p>
              <p>At the age of 34, The russian champion, competed as a crossfitter, created his own competition, launched a brand of wightlifting bars and plates and have even been part of
              a couple television shows. <br><b>So aside, from being
              an incredible athlete, he is now excelling as a Bussines-man.</b> </p>
              <br>
              <h3>4-Fans' relation</h3>
              <p>What set Klokov apart from all other weightlifters or athletes in general, its his great interaction with his followers.
              <br>With over 300 seminars, he travelled throughout the world to get in touch with his fans and give some from his great knowledge. </p>
              <p>Besides, He set challenges and get suggestion and work for them, to keep the excitement and inspiration. Add to that, he created a training camp
              that has allows anybody to be part of and spend 10 days with the russian legend and get deeper into his world.</p>


